<item>
            <title>[LU-5048] kernel/ext4 patch (ext4-mballoc-extra-checks.patch) is incomplete for latest SLES distros, and causes OSTs to be put in read-only mode due to wrong inconsistencies detected</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5048</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It has been discovered that an incomplete kernel/ext4 patch (ext4-mballoc-extra-checks.patch) has been provided for latest SLES distros, and causes OSTs to be put in read-only mode due to wrong inconsistencies detected like following :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;May 7 17:45:59 fsl2-oss1 kernel: [109553.943182] LDISKFS-fs error (device sde): ldiskfs_mb_generate_from_pa:3526: comm ll_ost_io03_013: lost preallocations: count 1, bb_prealloc_nr 2, skip 0
May 7 17:45:59 fsl2-oss1 kernel: [109553.943352] Aborting Journal on device sde-8.
May 7 17:45:59 fsl2-oss1 kernel: [109553.943460 LDISKFS-fs (sde): Remounting filesystem read-only
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment>SLES11SP2, SLES11SP3</environment>
        <key id="24681">LU-5048</key>
